<p>For each of the techniques below, get comfortable by being able to remove &amp; add the individual left-hand finger noted in each heading â€“ for each of the four chords. Once you feel comfortable with this, try to play freely using these four chords - in any order you want, using any strumming pattern you want! Add &amp; remove the noted finger as you desire. Then learn the next technique â€“ and return to the improvisational play, this time switching up which fingers youâ€™re removing or adding.</p>

<p>The end result is ideally the ability to freely jump between these four chords, but do so in a way where youâ€™re always able to add interesting flourish via the techniques shown here.</p>

